Three men aged between 25 and 32 were arrested on  Tuesday for the murder of Pietermaritzburg businessman, Gary Moodley (62). KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala, said the trio are expected to appear in the Pietermaritzburg Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday. It is believed there’s a fourth person still be to arrested. A reliable source told The Witness that the police and private security company worked together to make an arrest. Moodley who owned Mama’s Cookies with his partner was found inside his car with a gunshot wound in the chest just after 1:30 am on May 2. According to sources, he was driving out of the Invesco Centre from Cubana night club when he had an altercation with about four men by the exit gate of the centre.